George Lyle wrote:

> Considering that the life of CV joints is usually over 100K miles
> (sometimes _way_ over), there is probably not enough data out there for
> the time that the reman axles have been available.
> 
> I'm a bit suspicious of the idea of "remanufacturing" CV joints.  Sounds
> to me like they are taking old axles, keeping the OK CVs, and making up
> the deficit with new CVs.  Could be a good deal, could be a
> failure in
> 1000 miles.


I'll enter an experienced disagreement here.

Back when I was in the business, I probably installed 25 or 30 
remanufactured halfshafts.  VW, Toyota, American stuff...  Never had a 
failure.  Never.

